text: Man-Made Women is a 1928 American silent comedy drama film directed by Paul L. Stein and starring Leatrice Joy. It was produced by Cecil B. DeMille and Ralph Block and distributed through Pathé Exchange. The film is preserved at the Library of Congress.Catalog of Holdings The American Film Institute Collection and The United Artists Collection at The Library of Congress, p. 111, c.1978 by The American Film Institute ==Cast== *Leatrice Joy as Nan Payson *H.
